    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "609f6af2_a4a0a05b",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/cursor.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 33,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-30T02:12:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: when looking from the outside of the package, the diff between Cursor() and NewCursor() is not immediately by looking at func names. I think I\u0027d make the diff more clear by renaming this func to ParseCursorToken, CursorFromToken or something along those lines.\n\nAlso ideally, if one looks at this func and the one that produces a token, they are obviously represent a pair. We already have a pattern in pbutil: XXXName and ParseXXXName, so how about \"CursorToken\" and \"ParseCursorToken\"?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 33,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 33,
        "endChar": 11
      },
      "revId": "058f5d1e033b85218c00048f6de913129c49c6e2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e75805ca_4a617235",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/cursor.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 33,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-30T04:17:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "judging by the CL based on this one, we really need just two functions\n\n  func PageToken(position ...string) string\n  func ParsePageToken(pageToken string) []string",
      "parentUuid": "609f6af2_a4a0a05b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 33,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 33,
        "endChar": 11
      },
      "revId": "058f5d1e033b85218c00048f6de913129c49c6e2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e0919cf7_e76d7a60",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/cursor.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 33,
      "author": {
        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-30T19:00:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That somewhat breaks the black box of the cursor abstraction, doesn\u0027t it? That is, by doing this we are binding tokens to []string positions (and only []string positions); at that point, it seems we might as well remove the Cursor proto entirely.",
      "parentUuid": "e75805ca_4a617235",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 33,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 33,
        "endChar": 11
      },
      "revId": "058f5d1e033b85218c00048f6de913129c49c6e2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "95eac9e8_6dafc54a",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/cursor.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 35,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-30T02:12:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "let\u0027s return nil instead and make other functions tolerate nil cursor (L53 does that already)\nthis is consistent with the general Golang principle that zero values are useful",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 35,
        "startChar": 9,
        "endLine": 35,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "058f5d1e033b85218c00048f6de913129c49c6e2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "71a284cc_8befa621",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/cursor.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 35,
      "author": {
        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-30T19:00:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I considered that too... the thing is, we have to be able to handle a nil position too, and that pretty naturally means \"start at the beginning\". If we make nil cursor mean the same as a cursor with a nil position, that seems to introduce ambiguity and more room for errors (so in that sense, I might even prefer to change L53 to be simply c.Position)... WDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "95eac9e8_6dafc54a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 35,
        "startChar": 9,
