    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "eeaa8b94_b7576f30",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/proto/common.proto",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 23,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-30T02:12:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "imagine:\n\n1) db contains items a, b, c\n2) first page was requested with page size 2. token \"c\" is returned\n3) item bb is inserted., so the items are a, b, bb, c\n4) second page is requested. the client never sees bb\n\nfrom this perspective, it is better to make it exclusive. also it is simpler to implement, since we don\u0027t have to fetch pageSize+1 items.\n\nthis would be consistent with buildbucket",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 23,
        "startChar": 40,
        "endLine": 23,
        "endChar": 49
      },
      "revId": "058f5d1e033b85218c00048f6de913129c49c6e2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "da7f4932_0352ae3a",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/proto/common.proto",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 23,
      "author": {
        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-30T02:29:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Don\u0027t we have this same problem regardless of inclusive or exclusive though?\n\nThat is, suppose we have a, b, c, and a page size of 2 is requested, so token for \"b\" is returned. If item aa is inserted, the client will never see aa either.\n\nThis is also related to the discussion on the ListTestResults CL.",
      "parentUuid": "eeaa8b94_b7576f30",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 23,
        "startChar": 40,
        "endLine": 23,
        "endChar": 49
      },
      "revId": "058f5d1e033b85218c00048f6de913129c49c6e2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "41efed01_b2bfe844",
        "filename": "resultdb/internal/proto/common.proto",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 23,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-30T04:17:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "if it is aa, then i think i\u0027d be less surprised, since I\u0027ve seen items between a and b already. but if b is the last item i\u0027ve seen and when I am asking for more, i\u0027d expect things after b and bb is clearly after b. I guess what i am trying to say is, with exclusive cursor, what we return is fresher (we see bb) than with inclusive cursor (we don\u0027t see bb); and fresher is better. WDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "da7f4932_0352ae3a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 23,
        "startChar": 40,
        "endLine": 23,
        "endChar": 49
      },
      "revId": "058f5d1e033b85218c00048f6de913129c49c6e2",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
